Blood Rain Flat Check.command:
const flatcheckName = "Blood Rain";
const flatCheckDC = 14;

const flatCheckRoll = await new Roll('1d20').evaluate();

if (game.dice3d) {
  await game.dice3d.showForRoll(flatCheckRoll, game.user, true);
}

const flatCheckRollResult = flatCheckRoll.result < flatCheckDC
  ? 'Failure'
  : 'Success';

  const successText = `Roll Result: ${flatCheckRoll.total} - ${flatCheckRollResult}<hr>Cloud cover increases fully, and at some point during the night, what appears to be blood rains down on Willowshore. This "blood" seemingly coats everything with a layer of gore. Any PC who witnesses the blood rain must immediately attempt a save against the effects of the crimson moon, taking a -4 circumstance penalty to the save if they're out in the rain. A PC whose frightened condition increases as the result of this saving throw becomes fleeing for 1 minute and must attempt to escape to an indoor location. The blood rain ends after a few minutes, transitioning back to overcast skies for the remainder of the night. Fallen rain reverts to normal water once the bloody rain ends.`;
  const failText = `Roll Result: ${flatCheckRoll.total} - ${flatCheckRollResult}<hr>No Rain this evening, just the normal crimson moon effects.`;

const hidden = true;

const content = flatCheckRoll.result < flatCheckDC
  ? failText
  : successText;

await ChatMessage.create({
  content: content,
  whisper: hidden ? ChatMessage.getWhisperRecipients("GM").map((u) => u.id) : null,
  blind: hidden
});

